Book of Hours, Use of Utrecht

Free Library of Philadelphia, Lewis E 91. Netherlands, Late 15th century. This manuscript is a late fifteenth-century Dutch book of hours for the Use of Utrecht with a calendar for the Use of Maastricht. Occasional corrections or additions are written in the lower margin with points of insertion marked in the text, possibly by the scribe. Two miniatures, a Pieta and a penitent David, are by a much later artist.
